Development Board: Freescale Kinetis EKK20 from Manley

http://www.manley.com.cn/

Overview
--------

Drivers:

  o Console
  o Clock
  o Flexbus
  o TFT LCD
  o SD Card

BSP variants:
  dk_k20           - place code and data into internal ROM(128KB)
  dk_k60           - place code and data into internal ROM(256KB)
                     By default this board contains MK20DX128VL,
                     which has to be manually replaced with MK60DX256
                     if developer wants to select dk_k60.
                     But developer should be careful to do that because
                     the board‘s pad is frangible.
  dk_k60_psram     - place code and data into internal ROM(256KB)，
                     and place bbs into externl psram at address 0x80000000
                     RTEMS has to be configured with
                      FREESCALE_KINETIS_USING_PSRAM=1
                     and patched with fix-bugs-of-psram.patch (based on commit: 05461a)

Tool-chain used for development
-------------------------------

  arm-rtems5-gcc (GCC) 7.5.0 20191114 (RTEMS 5, RSB 5.1, Newlib 7947581)

  o For dk_k20:
  ../../../src/rtems/configure  --prefix=//opt/rtems/5 \
    --enable-maintainer-mode --target=arm-rtems5  --disable-cxx \
    --enable-tests=samples --disable-networking --enable-rtemsbsp=dk_k20

  o For dk_k60:
  ../../../src/rtems/configure  --prefix=//opt/rtems/5 \
    --enable-maintainer-mode --target=arm-rtems5  --disable-cxx \
    --enable-tests=samples --disable-networking --enable-rtemsbsp=dk_k60

  o For dk_k60_psram:
  ../../../src/rtems/configure  --prefix=//opt/rtems/5 \
    --enable-maintainer-mode --target=arm-rtems5  --disable-cxx \
    --enable-tests=samples --disable-networking --enable-rtemsbsp=dk_k60_psram \
    TMS570_USE_HWINIT_STARTUP=1

